              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>29</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-00MA</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00MA.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Non-empty sets and surjections">Non-empty sets and <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjections</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The unique <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[!_A\colon  A\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \not =\varnothing ]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-00MA/0</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MA-0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is nonempty, so that we have some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>. We must show that for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in {\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[!_A{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}=i]]></fr:tex>. Letting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i=0]]></fr:tex> be the unique element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we may set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:= a]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 <html:p>Conversely, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[!_A\colon  A\to {\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is surjective, we know that there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[!_A=0]]></fr:tex>; therefore, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is nonempty.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
