            <fr:title text="Surjection">Surjection</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is said to be <html:em><html:strong>surjective</html:strong></html:em> or a<html:em><html:strong>surjection</html:strong></html:em> when for we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists  a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>. A function satisfying this condition is written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
